  <TITLE>losing unsaved changes when modifying table definition</TITLE>
  <DESCRIPTION>I am running docker latest (2021-6-9). When I add new rows to a table and then change the table definition (changing a column, adding a column,...) without saving, the table refreshes and the new rows are lost. This is quite annoying. I'm not sure which ux I'd prefer. Displaying a warning when adding/editing a column and there are unsaved changes would be OK (&quot;you will lose unsaved changes to your content if you proceed to change the table definition&quot;). Would be even better if I could just change the definition without losing my unsaved changes, but that's probably harder to accomplish. I hit this issue when I needed to add a new option to a column of type SingleSelect when adding a new row.</DESCRIPTION>
